om/api/questions/11989/relationships/activeRevision"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4579","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"packs":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/packs","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/packs"}},"revisions":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/revisions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/revisions"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11989"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"99914"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"1987"},{"type":"tags","id":"1993"},{"type":"tags","id":"11691"},{"type":"tags","id":"12922"},{"type":"tags","id":"13209"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6873"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6911"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9887"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10002"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13348"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48261"},{"type":"contributions","id":"51469"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4579/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"118096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 54-year-old woman presents to the Psychiatry outpatient clinic for electroconvulsive therapy (ECT) treatments for her refractory depression, after failing trials of two antidepressants. She has a medical history of deep vein thrombosis one year ago, for which she received anticoagulation. She has no other significant medical history, in particular no cardiovascular disease or stroke. She has no evidence of raised intracranial pressure. She does not take any regular medications and has been fasting for more than eight hours.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her BMI is 21 kg/m2.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe will need to be counselled about potential side effects of the treatment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following side effects is she most likely to experience?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Headache","Pulmonary embolism","Palpitations","Muscle twitching","Anterograde amnesia"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EElectroconvulsive therapy is a fairly benign procedure that is highly efficacious. The most common side effects after ECT are \u003Cstrong\u003Eheadache\u003C/strong\u003E, nausea and vomiting, muscle soreness and confusion. In the Scottish ECT Accreditation Network (SEAN), which is the largest high-quality, service-level dataset available, headache is the most frequently reported side effect of ECT (20\u201328% of episodes across recent years), while memory problems (including anterograde and retrograde amnesia complaints) are next most common (~18\u201321%).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epulmonary embolism\u003C/strong\u003E is not a side effect of ECT. While there has been some literature surrounding the use of ECT in patients with a known DVT, the risk of dislodging a DVT and causing a PE during ECT is extremely minimal in modern practice. This is because patients are given a muscle relaxant, so there is usually no muscle contraction at all during the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPalpitations\u003C/strong\u003E or other cardiovascular phenomena such as acute myocardial infarctions can rarely occur. If they occur, it is most commonly immediately post-ictal or during the actual seizure itself. Arrhythmias account for most of the rare deaths associated with ECT.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMuscle twitching\u003C/strong\u003E is not a reported adverse effect of ECT. Instead, muscle soreness is more common due to the administration of muscle relaxant agents during the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile cognitive dysfunction is commonly experienced following ECT, it usually manifests as transient disorientation or retrograde amnesia. The memory loss is usually reversible and resolves within 6 months. \u003Cstrong\u003EAnterograde amnesia\u003C/strong\u003E (difficulty forming new memories) can occur but is less common than headache. When it does occur, anterograde amnesia typically affects the ability to form new memories for a short period after each ECT session, rather than causing long-term memory impairment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The most common side effects of ECT are headache, nausea and vomiting, muscle soreness and confusion.","Headache occurs in approximately 45% of patients following ECT, while anterograde amnesia is less common and typically resolves within 6 months."],"references":["Public Health Scotland. Scottish ECT Accreditation Network (SEAN): Reporting on data from January 2022 to May 2023. 21 Nov 2023. Available at: https://publichealthscotland.scot/media/23698/final-sean-reporting-on-data-from-january-2022-to-may-2023_nov-2023.pdf","Ghaziuddin N, Walter G. Electroconvulsive Therapy in Children and Adolescents: Oxford University Press; 2013","Lisanby, S. H., Maddox, J. H., Prudic, J., Devanand, D. P., \u0026 Sackeim, H. A. (2000). The Effects of Electroconvulsive Therapy on Memory of Autobiographical and Public Events. Archives of General Psychiatry, 57(6), 581\u2013590. https://doi.org/10-1001/pubs.Arch%20Gen%20Psychiatry-ISSN-0003-990x-57-6-yoa8422"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"99914"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11989"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/explanationMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/118096/relationships/explanationMedia"}}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"99914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/99914"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-10-05T18:06:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-10-06T12:23:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4579"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/99914/item","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/99914/relationships/item"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"118096"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/99914/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/99914/relationships/content"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/group","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/group"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/heading","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/heading"}},"ancestors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/ancestors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/ancestors"}},"parents":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/parents","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/parents"}},"children":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/children","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/children"}},"descendants":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/descendants","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1/relationships/descendants"}},"curricula":{"links":{